# Nginx Reverse Proxy

A reverse proxy sits in front of backend servers, forwarding client requests and returning responses. Nginx is the most common reverse proxy — it handles SSL termination, load balancing, caching, and request routing while backends focus on application logic.

## Basic Reverse Proxy

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}
```

## Upstream Groups (Load Balancing)

Define a group of backend servers in an `upstream` block:

```nginx
upstream backend {
    # Load balancing method (default: round-robin)
    least_conn;

    server 10.0.0.1:3000 weight=5;
    server 10.0.0.2:3000 weight=3;
    server 10.0.0.3:3000 max_fails=3 fail_timeout=30s;
    server 10.0.0.4:3000 backup;
}

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}
```

## Load Balancing Methods

| Method | Directive | Behavior |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| Round-robin | (default) | Distribute evenly, respects `weight` |
| Least connections | `least_conn` | Send to server with fewest active connections |
| IP hash | `ip_hash` | Same client IP always goes to same server (session affinity) |
| Generic hash | `hash $key` | Hash a custom key (e.g., `$request_uri`) |
| Random | `random two least_conn` | Pick 2 random servers, choose by least connections |

## Server Parameters

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| `weight=N` | 1 | Relative weight for load balancing |
| `max_fails=N` | 1 | Failed attempts before marking down |
| `fail_timeout=Ns` | 10s | Time window for max_fails AND unavailability duration |
| `max_conns=N` | 0 | Max simultaneous connections (0=unlimited) |
| `backup` | — | Only used when all primary servers are down |
| `down` | — | Permanently marks server as unavailable |

## Proxy Headers

Always set these headers so backends know about the real client:

```nginx
# Essential proxy headers
proxy_set_header Host $host;
proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
```

- **Host**: The original Host header from the client
- **X-Real-IP**: The actual client IP address
- **X-Forwarded-For**: Chain of IP addresses through proxies
- **X-Forwarded-Proto**: `http` or `https` — so backends know if the original request was secure

## WebSocket Proxying

WebSocket connections require the Upgrade and Connection headers:

```nginx
location /ws/ {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_read_timeout 86400s;  # keep connection alive for 24h
    proxy_send_timeout 86400s;
}
```

## Timeouts

```nginx
location / {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    proxy_connect_timeout 60s;   # time to establish connection
    proxy_send_timeout 60s;      # time between write operations
    proxy_read_timeout 60s;      # time between read operations
}
```

## Buffering

```nginx
location / {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    proxy_buffering on;                # buffer responses (default: on)
    proxy_buffer_size 4k;              # buffer for response headers
    proxy_buffers 8 4k;                # number and size of response buffers
    proxy_busy_buffers_size 8k;        # max buffers actively sending
    proxy_max_temp_file_size 1024m;    # max temp file for buffered responses
}
```

Disable buffering for streaming/SSE:

```nginx
location /events/ {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    proxy_buffering off;
    proxy_cache off;
}
```

## Keepalive Connections to Backends

```nginx
upstream backend {
    server 127.0.0.1:3000;
    keepalive 32;  # keep 32 idle connections per worker
}

server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Connection "";
    }
}
```

## Caching Proxied Responses

```nginx
proxy_cache_path /var/cache/nginx levels=1:2 keys_zone=app_cache:10m max_size=1g inactive=60m;

server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend;
        proxy_cache app_cache;
        proxy_cache_valid 200 60m;
        proxy_cache_valid 404 10m;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_cache_control;
        proxy_cache_key "$scheme$request_method$host$request_uri";
        add_header X-Cache-Status $upstream_cache_status;
    }
}
```

## Failover

```nginx
upstream backend {
    server 10.0.0.1:3000;
    server 10.0.0.2:3000;
}

server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend;
        proxy_next_upstream error timeout http_502 http_503 http_504;
        proxy_next_upstream_tries 3;
        proxy_next_upstream_timeout 10s;
    }
}
```
